@SBK

We tried an extra-hot version of ground cayenne pepper in some of our potted plants, but it didn’t seem to deter squirrels. 

Then I read somewhere that the pepper gets in the animal’s eyes and that they will literally scratch their eyes out because of the pain. That might not be true, but I didn’t want to chance it.

