@Michelle. I winced as well, but just took it as an old-fashioned saying, as Linda Jo says. 

@Melanie  "Mrs." used along with someone's last name is a title of respect, but used along with "the," as in the clue, feels dehumanizing. Ditto "the wife" rather than "your wife." 

We used to do something similar when we'd say "the parents" rather than "my parents." For similar reasons.

@Lynn

I've referred to my wife in this forum as "The MRS." and I don't think it's dehumanizing.  I don't want to use her name here (although being identified was more of a worry when I was still working and participating more in other comment sections).

I don't feel it's any different than saying "my wife".  I'm sure there are hundreds of people who disagree with me, but I'm really not seeing a problem.  If she similarly referred to me as "the hubby" or as MOL says (if I recall) the "DH", I wouldn't take offense.

